\begin{frame}[fragile]{Data types}
\pause
R can handle data of a variety of types: \pause Numbers like \rcode{42.6}, \pause characters like \rcode{"R rocks"}, \pause complex numbers like \rcode{8+4i}, \pause categories with \rcode{as.factor(c("blue", "green"))}, \pause logical or boolean values \rcode{c(TRUE, FALSE)} \pause and a few others. \pause They should usually not be mixed. \pause For example, you can't perform algebraic computation on characters:
